        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "400 g medjool or soft dates, pitted"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Put the dates in a saucepan and add enough boiling water to cover them. Place the pan over a medium heat and simmer the dates gently for about 5 minutes or until they are really soft."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Meanwhile, toast the almonds, if using, for about 5 minutes in a dry frying pan over a low heat. Set them aside to cool slightly, then chop them roughly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tip the dates into a sieve to drain and discard the water. Transfer the dates to a food processor and leave them to cool for a few minutes. Add the nut butter, butter, maple syrup and cocoa powder and blend until smooth. Stir in the chopped nuts and dried cherries, if using."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lightly grease a 25cm square shallow baking tray and line it with baking paper. Spoon the mixture into the tray and spread the surface flat with a spatula. Cover with another layer of baking paper and put the fudge in the freezer for 3 hours to set."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove the fudge from the freezer and let it defrost for 5 minutes before cutting it into small squares. Put the squares in a freezer-proof container and keep them in the freezer until needed. Allow the fudge to defrost for 5 minutes before you eat it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "You can leave out the almonds and cherries if you want something plainer or you can add other dried fruit or nuts, such as sultanas, dried apricots, hazelnuts, pecans and so on. Medjool dates do add a fab flavour but you can also use soft pitted dates which are cheaper. The fudge can be kept in the freezer for up to three months – if you’re really strong-willed! 137 calories per piece."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
